        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 11:11PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1110 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Statesville, moving southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Statesville, Troutman, Lake Norman State Park, and Scotts.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
the Piedmont of North Carolina.</instruction>
